Pihole use cron jobs to do some tasks.
But why use cron, when you have systemd?

I basically created service/timer files that does the same thing that the cron jobs are doing for the Pihole.
This could be handy when you otherwise dont use cron at all.

The origional post from reddit:
https://www.reddit.com/r/pihole/comments/1pe3jsa/cron_to_systemd/

The cron jobs in question:
https://github.com/pi-hole/pi-hole/blob/master/advanced/Templates/pihole.cron

